title: I’ve been asked to make an official Iron Maiden Pop-up for their anniversary book

images.description:
My next (official) pop-up publication is for the Iron Maiden Piece of Mind 40th Anniversary Deluxe Oversized Edition graphic novel. This will be released anytime soon.

No need to say that I'm super proud that z2 Comics asked me to make a pop-up for this official Iron Maiden publication! The first spread of this luxurious book contains my pop-up and it came out great!

In this post I’ll share some of the process of making this pop-up design. And a video of the box case below this post.

Cover art by Jason Edmiston

Making of the first concept part 1

This a time lapse of the very first concept I made for this pop-up. I start with a bunch of prints that I can use to cut out pieces. WHen I'm happy with the design, I continue tracing the parts on my computer so I can replicate and fine-tune the mechanisms. When this all works, I continue adding artwork (Cover art by Jason Edmiston) to all the parts on both sides. the prints for my concepts are ste to 50% tranparancy so I'm not wasting any toner but it also makes it less messy to work with and theres room for notes.

title: Saw this and decided to do my own analysis...

images.description:
Clearly, the conclusion being insinuated here is that the party that wins the KY gubernatorial election will win the presidential election in the following year.

I, knowing this is BS from the graphic presented, decided to do my own analysis.

To determine if there is a relationship between the winning party in KY and the following presidential election year, I performed a quick and dirty logistic regression analysis. First, the data...
This data goes through the 2019 to 2020 elections and shows the winning party in each election for KY and the following Pres election.

Here are some real quick stats. There have been 41 elections since 1859. I chose this as a cutoff period as that's when it seems the R & D parties had sufficiently established a two party system.

Of the 41 elections that have taken place, the KY gov race was followed by a win in the white house by the same party 24 times, or 59% of the time.

I've never told anyone about the stuff from when I was a kid. I was abused from before I was born (I was born addicted) until I was 28 and that abuse included sexual abuse.

My partner and I fight about sex a lot and he knows about the stuff with my ex but he doesn't know about the stuff from when I was a kid and the way he has also (unknowingly) contributed to my trauma. Every time we fight about a dry spell I find a different reason for it that doesn't involve my history of assault. Partially because it feels like an excuse, and partially because it feels like I'm asking him to take responsibility for things he didn't do.

That's going to change next week. Hopefully he is receptive to it. I'm gonna read it to my therapist before I read it in couples counseling but if anyone else can help me with editing I'm open to it. I'm worried that he'll take it as an attack and it'll add another layer of trauma.

Thanks for reading. I hope you have a good day, or night, whatever it is where you are.

title: Why sub-1qt copper saucepans or splayed sautes are crucial: 5-minute gochujang garlic buffalo sauce for two

images.description:
1. Sweat minced garlic in butter
2. Add gochujang, rice vinegar, lime juice, ketchup, honey, brown sugar, soy sauce, mirin, fish sauce, sesame oil, seasoned seaweed mushroom paste, hot sauce of choice (Melinda's ghost)
3. Swirl in knob of cold butter off heat to emulsify
4. Toss with wings, scallions, sesame seeds

You need the narrow floor space of a tiny saucepan or splayed saute to avoid scorching a small quantity of sauce like this without constant whisking.

images.description: This is my current crown jewel, a early 1980s Riga Mini. With gear selection on left handlebar, thus completely disabling any possibility for me to indicate my turns. Dumb and marvelous.
Added a custom-ordered LED controller for the headlight. The electrical system is 6V, thus it can't drive LEDs natively.

A "before" pic next to another beauty, 1987 Riga 13. Yes, the engine is still manufactured in China and can be installed as cheap kits. The original engines are far superior in quality though, this engine has run for 4 seasons and about 6000km, no sign of it being tired.

title: Alan Lee's Work with Tolkien's Work ;)

images.description: Alan Lee is an English artist from Middlesex, England, born in 1947 and is blessedly still cavorting around the Lakes District (maybe).  I've seen a lot of Tolkien artists and I like some of Lee's stuff more than some of those other artists.  I appreciate his take on the hobbits as they look gnarlier, uglier (?); certainly a different perception of the character than I had imagine as a kid when I first saw Bakshi's Lord of the Rings and then later when I read the books themselves.

title: Russian war criminal killed in car explosion in occupied Luhans'k, Ukraine

images.description:
The Main Directorate of Intelligence of the Ministry of Defence of Ukraine informs:

"On 8 November, 2023 at 08:40 a.m. (local time), due to a car explosion, the deputy of the so-called "supreme soviet of the lnr*" from the russian liberal democratic party, mikhail yuryevich filiponenko, was eliminated.

He was involved in the organization of torture camps in the occupied territories of Luhans'k oblast, where prisoners of war and civilian hostages were subjected to inhumane torture, and filiponenko himself personally brutally tortured people.

The war criminal filiponenko, who previously held the position of the so-called "minister of internal affairs" of the lnr* terrorist entity, lived at No. 48 Parashutna Street in the city of Luhans'k.

The special operation for the liquidation of the executioner filiponenko was implemented jointly with representatives of the resistance movement.

As a result of the morning explosion, filiponenko died on the spot.

The Main Directorate of Intelligence of the Ministry of Defence of Ukraine warns:
all addresses of traitors and places of their service to terrorist russia in the temporarily occupied territories of Ukraine are known!

The Main Directorate of Intelligence states that all war criminals and collaborators will receive a fair retribution!

The hunt continues!  Glory to Ukraine!"

A better bert slide! One thing that's a downside is that because I can't get a lot of speed in such a short area, I lose some momentum and the board comes to a slow or stop. I wanna try this out in a larger area to really rip.

Almost 180 switchblade! I figured something out with my catch-foot placement. Originally I had it way closer to the edge and towards a corner, but no. The catch foot has to be closer inland and in the middle. The balance is pretty bad with this one, but we can work on better balance.

Some skate sounds if anyone is interested. I've noticed that on my larger board, it feels more like I'm riding something, while on this one, it feels like I am something, if that makes sense? 

Sorry I've been a bit absent. November is a busy month for me, and I've had a lot of homework and other things going on. I still skate, just not as much as the summer. I'm hoping that when my winter break starts, I can get a lot more time along with submitting college applications. Speaking of college, wish me good luck on Thursday, doing something about my dream school :)
